<emphasis id="B953EAC40520621FFA443138FA728B61" bold="true" box="[1474,1500,564,604]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">L</emphasis>
. curvatus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26057BF0520621FF9173138F8948B61" box="[1681,1850,564,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B953EAC40520621FF9173138F94E8B61" box="[1681,1760,564,604]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">spec</emphasis>
. nov.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9836D60520621FFEF3316AF8E58BB3" blockId="2.[373,1871,462,1104]" box="[373,1867,614,654]" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">
<keyLead id="30D695E30520621FFEF3316AF8E58BB3" box="[373,1867,614,654]" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">- Caudal appendages not pale, conical i.e. regularly tapering from base to apex ... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
