<keyLead id="30D695E30520621FFEF33194F8958A1E" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">
4 (3). Caudal appendages slender and about three and a half times as long as it is wide at base. Pectoral colour pattern with three pairs of dark oblong spots close to ventro-lateral carina (fig. 7) ............................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D550520621FFA3731F7F92B8A1E" authorityName="J. Belle" authorityYear="1997" box="[1457,1669,763,803]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edentatus" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B953EAC40520621FFA3731F7F92B8A1E" box="[1457,1669,763,803]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">L. edentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26057BF0520621FF91731F7F8958A1E" box="[1681,1851,763,803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="91" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B953EAC40520621FF91731F7F94F8A1E" box="[1681,1761,763,803]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">spec</emphasis>
. nov.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9836D60520621FFEF03022F8918AB5" blockId="2.[373,1871,462,1104]" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">
<keyLead id="30D695E30520621FFEF03022F8918AB5" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">- Caudal appendages short, thick, conical and twice to two and a half times as long as it is wide at base...............................................................................................5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D32E730520621FFEF3309EF8928D72" pageId="2" pageNumber="91">
